Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> query
Rule 1     query -> select_stmt
Rule 2     select_stmt -> SELECT ID FROM ID

Terminals, with rules where they appear

FROM                 : 2
ID                   : 2 2
SELECT               : 2
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

query                : 0
select_stmt          : 1

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . query
    (1) query -> . select_stmt
    (2) select_stmt -> . SELECT ID FROM ID

    SELECT          shift and go to state 3

    query                          shift and go to state 1
    select_stmt                    shift and go to state 2

state 1

    (0) S' -> query .



state 2

    (1) query -> select_stmt .

    $end            reduce using rule 1 (query -> select_stmt .)


state 3

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT . ID FROM ID

    ID              shift and go to state 4


state 4

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT ID . FROM ID

    FROM            shift and go to state 5


state 5

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT ID FROM . ID

    ID              shift and go to state 6


state 6

    (2) select_stmt -> SELECT ID FROM ID .

    $end            reduce using rule 2 (select_stmt -> SELECT ID FROM ID .)

